postcontent: Selling an unbelievable find, one of the few US Property marked transferable M16's in the United States. This is an all factory original machine gun that was built by Colt in Hartford, CT in the late 1970's. This was sold to the Federal Government, and the widely accepted story is that these were issued to the Department of Energy (DOE) to protect nuke sites across the country. A small number of these were sold to civilians in the late 1980's. As you can see, this was a carried weapon and has some great patina and lots of character. If you are thinking about buying another M16, please ask if it is in dealer inventory - I have noticed other dealers play games with this simple fact.
